Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a
knife through, ~{15-20%mins}. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a
#colander{} and return to the #pan{}, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a
#lid{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} and
@British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

While the meat is cooking, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}(trimmed) and discard.
Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways
into small pieces.

Once the bacon is cooked, add the leek, carrot and @sliced mushrooms{180%grams}
to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook the chicken is cooked through
and the veg is softened, ~{7-8%mins}, stirring occasionally.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%min} more.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat your #grill{} to its highest temperature.

Once the veg has softened, stir in the @butter{20%grams} and @plain flour{2%tbsp}
into the pan and cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @wholegrain mustard{17%grams} (add less if
you'd prefer), @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{150%ml} and simmer for
~{3-4%mins}.

Pour the pie filling into an appropriately sized #oven dish{}. Spoon over the
mash, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out.

Grill until your pie is golden and bubbling, ~{3-4%mins}.

When everything's piping hot, share between your serving plates. Enjoy!